The Italian community in Malindi marked the 50th anniversary of the first satellite launch by Italian Space agency San Marco at Ungwana bay near Ngomeni Magarini sub county of Kilifi county.Present were four veterans who witnessed the historic satellite launch, their relatives and current staff of San Marco space agency.The guests included Franco Esposito, 74, alias Kasoso Baya, who earned his name while working as a manager at San Marco, and former techniciansLuiggi Riccardi,66, and Elio Altomarie, 84.Esposito told journalists that San Marco has been in the forefront of bringing Italian tourists to Malindi, some of whom have become permanent residents in Kenya.